Q: Why is stack called a Container Adaptor?

A:
Because stack does not store data itself.
It wraps another STL container (deque by default)
and provides a restricted interface that enforces
LIFO behavior.

Q: Why is deque the default container for stack?

A:
Because deque provides efficient O(1)
push_back(), pop_back(), and back() operations
without the reallocation issues of vector.


